 :tx/rationale "STEERING-LOOP ITEM 3 — OBSERVE RESPONSE NOISE: Agents universally use -q flag which suppresses ALL output after the first line, including concept membership and steering questions. The entire CCE steering mechanism is accidentally disabled by the noise-reduction flag. ROOT CAUSE: The observe command concatenates 10+ context blocks (connections, topological events, concept membership, gap line, steering question, crystallization feedback, spec-connection, reconciliation, hypothesis predictions) into one response. The -q flag suppresses the guidance footer but the primary response is still 8+ lines. Agents suppress because the signal-to-noise ratio is too low. FIX: Split observe output into PRIMARY (3 lines: what was stored, concept membership, steering question) and SECONDARY (--verbose: everything else). CRITICAL: -q must suppress footer but NOT primary. Currently -q suppresses everything past line 1, meaning concept assignments are invisible. VERIFICATION: Agent using -q sees concept:X and steering question. Agent without flags sees full detail. INTERACTION: This is the highest-leverage single fix — it un-hides the entire CCE from agents who use -q."
